   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/political/Jones_Sam_Houston_T36.abs.pdf">In the interview, Jones discusses his political campaign of 1940; changes he made
            while in office; Huey Long's political following; views on social welfare; government
            corruption; Jones' second gubernatorial campaign; Jones' executive secretary, Cocheran;
            Jones' wife's role in his career; his birth and family background; state senator W.D.
            Cotton's role in bridge over Calcasieu River; development of schools and buildings
            during his administration.</abstract>
